               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary><p>
  This single folio contains the beginning of the <title xml:lang="sa">Yogaśataka</title>, a medical text attributed to <persName xml:lang="sa">Nāgārjuna</persName> or <persName xml:lang="sa">Vararuci</persName>, with a commentary in <term xml:lang="sa">tripāṭha</term> format. It seems to be a lithograph, printed only on one side of a small piece of cardstock.
</p>
<p>
  The opening verses of the commentary inform us that it was authored by <persName xml:lang="sa">Pūrṇasena</persName>. At the <ref target="https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/btv1b10090954q/f34.item">end of Sanscrit 1307</ref>, another manuscript of the same work, the title of the commentary is given as <title xml:lang="sa">Abhidhānacintāmaṇi</title>.
</p></summary>
                  
